  "prompt": "I scored 72% in 10th and 88% in 12 can I be able to became ias officer?",
  "response": "Yes, you can definitely become an IAS (Indian Administrative Service) officer if you scored 72% in 10th grade and 88% in 12th grade. The eligibility criteria for the IAS exam primarily focus on the following:\n\n1. **Educational Qualification**: You need to have a bachelor's degree from a recognized university. Your performance in 10th and 12th grades is not a deciding factor for IAS eligibility, but a solid academic background can be beneficial for your overall profile.\n\n2. **Age Limit**: You must be within the prescribed age limit (generally 21 to 32 years for the general category, with certain relaxations for reserved categories).\n\n3. **Citizenship**: You must be a citizen of India or meet specific citizenship criteria.\n\nOnce you fulfill the educational qualification, you can prepare for the UPSC Civil Services Examination, which consists of three stages: Preliminary Exam, Mains Exam, and Personality Test (Interview).\n\nIt's important to focus on your graduation and then start preparing for the IAS exam. Many aspirants begin their preparation during their undergraduate studies. Good luck with your endeavors!",
